      • getCSVItems

        public static java.util.List<Item> getCSVItems(java.lang.String fileLocation)
                                        throws CSVFormatException,
                                               java.io.IOException
        This static method takes a csv file location as input, which the user selects via a file chooser within the Intro GUI. The class throws exceptions when its detects an issue with the csv file; either the extension or the the format of the data within it.
        Parameters:
        fileLocation - - file location of the Item Property file as a string
        Returns:
        inventory - a list of Items, which can be passed to a Stock object to create an inventory
        Throws:
        CSVFormatException - - throws this exception for issues around csv file format and data
        java.io.IOException - - throws this exception when a problem is detected with IO
